---
// Arrow that flies out to the right and re-enters from the left, looping while hovered.
//
// Reproduced in CSS rather than ported from animate-ui. Pulling in React and a motion
// library to nudge an 18px arrow would ship a runtime and a hydration island for one
// hover, on a site that has neither.
//
// The wrapping .arr-clip is the whole trick: an 18px window with overflow hidden. The
// arrow leaves through its right edge and returns through its left, and the teleport
// between the two happens where nobody can see it. Without the clip the arrow would
// simply slide off across the paragraph.
//
// Styles and keyframes live in global.css under .btn-link, because scoped styles do not
// reach content rendered from MDX.
---
<span class="arr-clip" aria-hidden="true">
  <svg
    class="arr"
    viewBox="0 0 24 24"
    fill="none"
    stroke="currentColor"
    stroke-width="2"
    stroke-linecap="round"
    stroke-linejoin="round"
    focusable="false"
  >
    <path d="M5 12h14" />
    <path d="m12 5 7 7-7 7" />
  </svg>
</span>
